content:
Launching an LWC OmniScript from an OS Action on a Card

Beginning with Vlocity Insurance and Vlocity Health Winter '18, Vlocity Cards contains a configurable OmniScript Action (OS Action). The OS Action simplifies the process to navigate to an OmniScript from a card action.

To launch an LWC OmniScript with an OS Action in Lightning:

Follow the instructions on Configuring an OS Action.
Add the card to a Lightning page. See Adding a Vlocity Card to a Lightning or Community Page.
(Optional) To reload the card when the LWC OmniScript updates, see Reloading a Card After Updating an LWC OmniScript.

Beginning with Vlocity Insurance and Health Winter '20 and Vlocity CME Winter '20, Vlocity Cards supports launching an LWC OmniScript with an OS Action in a Community:

Create a community page with the URL /lwcos. 
Add a Vlocity LWC OmniScript Wrapper component to the /lwcos Community page.
Add the card to the Community page that launches the action, such as the Home page or Record Detail page.
(Optional) Reload the card when the LWC OmniScript updates.

Configuring an OS Action

Open the Vlocity Cards tab, and click on a version of a card to open the Card Designer.
Click Add OS Action in the Actions section of a card state
In the Id field, enter a unique name to distinguish the action from other actions in the Card Designer.
Choose an active OmniScript from the drop-down list. 
(Optional) Enter values for these properties:

Action Options: To add custom parameters, set conditions for when the OS Action displays, and configure optional settings for LWC enabled cards, select this checkbox.

Icon: Select a Vlocity icon or an SLDS icon to display next to the action link.
Open URL in: Select Current Window or New Tab/Window to indicate where to open the target URL.
